title: Part E
stimulusHtml: Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples and to score the response.
descriptions: The response does not state that real GDP in Davinskia will decrease and/or does not explain that actual inflation is greater than expected inflation, which means that the short-run aggregate supply curve will shift to the left (or the short-run Phillips curve will shift to the right) until expected inflation adjusts to actual inflation.

The response states that real GDP in Davinskia will decrease and explains that actual inflation is greater than expected inflation, which means that the short-run aggregate supply curve will shift to the left (or the short-run Phillips curve will shift to the right) until expected inflation adjusts to actual inflation.
